    <abstract id="aspace_bacd8566e6a5e80a333824c89b96e88f">In 1979 the staff of the New-York Historical Society began an organizing drive with District 65, United Automobile Workers of America. Victory in the union elections led to contract negotiations, and the staff conducted a six month strike before signing a collective bargaining agreement in 1980. This collection contains newspaper clippings, photographs, minutes from the negotiating committee, copies of contracts, and leaflets.</abstract>
